ch as dodge ball.  We're still headed in the wrong direction with gender neutral bathrooms in states like California.  Our own political leaders advocacy for our public school system rings hollow starting at the top with President Obama sending his own kids to a private school. We spend more per student on education than any country in the world, while our rankings are abysmal American students rank 25th in math, 17th in science and 14th in reading compared to students in 27 industrialized countries and it's getting worse. Fully 81% of that money goes to teachers and teacher benefits.  This country would be much better off without public education.  Fact:  some of our smartest students have been home schooled, why parental involvement.  Although my kids went to public schools that were quite good, most are mediocre at best especially in urban centers. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1171" language="en" documentId="2734" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="jimjumpinflash" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:22PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="25" thumbsDown="0" origId="2734" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1171"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>